Title: Realistic Morning to Night

INT. APARTMENT KITCHEN - MORNING
A kettle clicks off on the stove.
MAYA folds a city map and slides it into a canvas tote.
JONAH checks his watch near the doorway.
MAYA
Did you print the permit form?
JONAH
It's in the blue folder.
MAYA
Good. Grab the tape measure too.

EXT. BUS STOP - MORNING
A city bus sighs to the curb as rain starts lightly.
DIANE jogs up with a clipboard under her coat.
MAYA holds the tote closed against the rain.
DIANE
If traffic is bad, we lose the loading window.
JONAH
Then we unload first and sort inside.

INT. COMMUNITY CENTER LOBBY - DAY
Stacked folding chairs block part of the entrance.
JONAH moves two stacks aside to clear a path.
MAYA marks door widths on the permit form.
DIANE sets a roll of gaffer tape on the front desk.
CUT TO:

INT. APARTMENT KITCHEN - NIGHT
A wet umbrella drips into the sink.
The permit form sits signed beside a ring of keys.
MAYA
Tomorrow we start at seven.
JONAH
I'll bring coffee.
